\f1\fs26 \ul \uc0\u8232 \ulnone Completed ISTQB Certified Tester Advanced Level - Test Management 3.0 After years in Software Testing, I was curious whether ISTQB still makes sense today. Sharing a few quick thoughts while it\'92s still fresh \uc0\u55357 \u56396  What worked well: - The program has been updated from 2011 to 2024 and the content\'a0feels much more relevant today - Plenty of international certification centres available - The online (at-home) exam is similar to the in-person exam, but can be scheduled for any business hour and quickly (within 5 days) - The syllabus gives a solid refresher on Testing within the SDLC - Packed with information, but great for a quick refresh - Examples of questions/answers really help to understand the exam logic and structure - Trial exam from partners are helpful to train your timing skill - Additional side-materials and apps(!) add real tremendous value for preparation \u55357 \u56539  What could be better: - The language is sometimes overly bureaucratic or academic - A few questions seem to require knowledge beyond the syllabus (e.g., TMMi, TPI), which feels useless for masses outside of corporates \u55356 \u57252  Summary: - For me, this certification is less about \'93a badge for the CV\'94 and more about refreshing terminology and revisiting how we think about processes and metrics - It\'92s also realistic to pass it through self-study - no formal training required for experienced Test Manager/QA Lead; just to be motivated for dozens of hours refreshing syllabus\'92 vocabulary and practicing timing using a simulator or examples \u55358 \u56733  Curious, do you find certifications like ISTQB actually useful in practice or if they\'92re more of a structured refresher? #ISTQB #TestManagement , Lesson learned: I\'92ve just completed the ISTQB Certified Tester Advanced Level - Test Management 3.0, Victor Ematin on LinkedIn \'95 2 min read\u8232 \ul \uc0\u8232 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7444420952987197441?updateEntityUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afs_updateV2%3A%28urn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7444420952987197441%2CFEED_DETAIL%2CEMPTY%2CDEFAULT%2Cfalse%29"}}{\fldrslt Completed ISTQB Certified Tester Advanced Level - Test Management 3.0\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \ul After years in Software Testing, I was curious whether ISTQB still makes sense today. Sharing a few quick thoughts while it\'92s still fresh\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \ul \uc0\u55357 \u56396  What worked well:\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \ul - The program has been updated from 2011 to 2024 and the content\'a0feels much more relevant today\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \ul - Plenty of international certification centres available\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \ul - The online (at-home) exam is similar to the in-person exam, but can be scheduled for any business hour and quickly (within 5 days)\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \ul - The syllabus gives a solid refresher on Testing within the SDLC\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \ul - Packed with information, but great for a quick refresh\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \ul - Examples of questions/answers really help to understand the exam logic and structure\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \ul - Trial exam from partners are helpful to train your timing skill\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \ul - Additional side-materials and apps(!) add real tremendous value for preparation\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \ul \uc0\u55357 \u56539  What could be better:\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \ul - The language is sometimes overly bureaucratic or academic\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \ul - A few questions seem to require knowledge beyond the syllabus (e.g., TMMi, TPI), which feels useless for masses outside of corporates\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \ul  \uc0\u55356 \u57252  Summary:\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \ul - For me, this certification is less about \'93a badge for the CV\'94 and more about refreshing terminology and revisiting how we think about processes and metrics\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \ul - It\'92s also realistic to pass it through self-study - no formal training required for experienced Test Manager/QA Lead; just to be motivated for dozens of hours refreshing syllabus\'92 vocabulary and practicing timing using a simulator or examples\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \ul \uc0\u55358 \u56733  Curious, do you find certifications like ISTQB actually useful in practice or if they\'92re more of a structured refresher?\ulnone \uc0\u8232 \u8232 }}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.linkedin.com/search/results/all/?keywords=%23istqb&origin=HASH_TAG_FROM_FEED"}}{\fldrslt 
