\f1\fs26 \ul \uc0\u8232 \ulnone Software 3.0: The Rise of Agent Engineering This study examines Andrej Karpathy's vision for the future of technology, marking the transition to what is defined as Software 3.0. In this new paradigm, traditional programming is replaced by large language models that serve as underlying operating systems, responding to human input rather than manual instructions. The key differences are as follows: - Vibe-coding: This approach allows hobbyists to quickly create applications. - Agent engineering: A professional discipline focused on managing complex AI workflows. While these tools are immensely powerful, they highlight the phenomenon of "serrated" intelligence, where models may excel at technical tasks but lack basic common sense. This underscores the idea that while AI may manage execution, humans remain crucial for providing architectural vision, aesthetic judgment, and strategic insight. Ultimately, this narrative serves as a guide for navigating a world where agent orchestration is becoming a more valuable skill than traditional syntax writing., Beyond Vibe-Coding:Dawn of Software3.0 & Agent Engineering\uc0\u8232 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7460450208943071232?updateEntityUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afs_updateV2%3A%28urn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7460450208943071232%2CFEED_DETAIL%2CEMPTY%2CDEFAULT%2Cfalse%29"}}{\fldrslt \ul Software 3.0: The Rise of Agent Engineering\ulnone \
