\f1\fs26 \ul \uc0\u8232 \ulnone From "Vibing" to Production: 5 Counter-Intuitive Truths About the New Era of Coding We have crossed the Rubicon into the Age of the Code Sneeze. For decades, software engineering was defined by the deliberate, manual labor of logic\'97a high-friction process of translating human thought into rigid syntax. Nowdays, as Andrej Karpathy famously noted, "writing software is as easy as sneezing." This "Karpathy Canon" advocates for a paradigm of "Accept All," where developers increasingly disengage from line-by-line authoring and trust agentic tools to orchestrate systems from natural language. But this effortless creation has birthed a massive sociological phenomenon: a crisis of maintenance. If code can be generated in a heartbeat, the bottleneck moves from the editor to the production environment. If writing code is now a commodity, why is operating it harder than ever? To survive this shift, we must move beyond the hype and embrace the strategic reality of building, testing, and operating software when AI holds the keyboard. 1. Moving Beyond the "Vibe" to the "Wipe" The industry is currently splitting into two distinct modalities: Vibe Coding and Wipe Coding. Vibe coding\'97building software by describing a general "vibe" to an AI\'97is a creative gestalt, much like a Bob Ross painting where "happy accidents" lead to rapid prototypes. It is perfect for exploration, but it possesses an inherent level of unmaintainability. The move to production requires Wipe Coding. This is the transition from "chatting with prompts" to a full AI partner with "hands" in the material substrate\'97running terminal commands, installing packages, and applying changes across entire file structures simultaneously. Wipe-coding (or Flow-state coding): A development style where the programmer stops writing code "by hand" line by line. AI "wipes" old abstractions and applies (wipes) new layers of code across many files at once. ...// details in the article below 2. Traditional TDD is Failing\'97Meet Observability-Driven Development (ODD) ...// details in the article below 3. Breaking the "Cycle of Self-Deception" with Property-Based Testing ...// details in the article below 4. The 10x Engineer is Now a 10x Operator ..// details in the article below 5. AI as the "Trojan Horse" for Modern Best Practices ..// details in the article below Conclusion: The Future is "Yes, And" Vibe Coding and Wipe Coding are not opposing camps. Vibe coding provides the spark of exploration; Wipe coding provides the rigor of production. Expertise hasn't been replaced; it has been redistributed toward context management, the curation of intention, and rapid evaluation. In this new era, the code is no longer the "Source of Truth"\'97it is merely the output. The developer is the Source of Intention. In a world where code is a commodity, are you prepared to stop being a writer and start being an architect of intention? , From "Vibing" to Production: 5 Counter-Intuitive Truths About the New Era of Coding, Victor Ematin on LinkedIn \'95 5 min read\uc0\u8232 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7460105294061158400?updateEntityUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afs_updateV2%3A%28urn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7460105294061158400%2CFEED_DETAIL%2CEMPTY%2CDEFAULT%2Cfalse%29"}}{\fldrslt \ul From "Vibing" to Production: 5 Counter-Intuitive Truths About the New Era of Coding\ulnone \
